cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper deals with on-orbit servicing and close-proximity formation flying missions, which are typical applications of robotics. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a monocular vision-based pose determination architecture, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper introduces a novel pose determination method based on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN), which is a popular AI technique. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the estimation of the pose of an uncooperative target spacecraft, which requires control and estimation techniques. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper introduces an image synthesis pipeline to generate high fidelity images of spacecraft 3D models, which involves graphics and rendering techniques.
